HEADWORD: Linoleic
<hw>Li*no"le*ic</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧*n⟦omac⟧"l⟦esl⟧*⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, or derived from, linoleum, or linseed
oil; specifically <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, designating an organic acid, a
thin yellow oil, found combined as a salt of glycerin in oils of
linseed, poppy, hemp, and certain nuts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

